@page "/"

<PageTitle>Faunex</PageTitle>

<section class="home-hero" aria-labelledby="home-title">
    <div class="home-hero__content">
        <p class="home-kicker">Multi-tenant auction infrastructure</p>
        <h1 id="home-title">Faunex</h1>
        <p class="home-lede">
            A regulated marketplace platform for specialist auctions, compliance-driven listings,
            and future tenant marketplaces across South Africa and Africa.
        </p>

        <div class="home-actions" aria-label="Primary actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/browse">Browse Listings</a>
            <a class="btn btn-outline-light btn-lg" href="/register">Create Account</a>
        </div>

        <dl class="home-snapshot" aria-label="Platform snapshot">
            <div>
                <dt>Tenant 1</dt>
                <dd>Storm Bird Auctions</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
                <dt>Model</dt>
                <dd>Auctions, listings, compliance</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
                <dt>Built For</dt>
                <dd>Birds, livestock, poultry, game</dd>
            </div>
        </dl>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="home-section home-section--intro" aria-labelledby="platform-heading">
    <div class="home-section__inner">
        <div class="home-section__copy">
            <p class="home-kicker home-kicker--dark">Platform first</p>
            <h2 id="platform-heading">One auction engine, many specialist marketplaces.</h2>
            <p>
                Faunex is designed as reusable marketplace infrastructure. Storm Bird Auctions is the first tenant,
                but the same foundation will support breeders, associations, conservation networks, livestock exchanges,
                poultry markets, and other regulated trading communities.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="home-capabilities" aria-label="Core platform capabilities">
            <article>
                <h3>Tenant Marketplaces</h3>
                <p>Independent branding, roles, categories, compliance rules, and future subscription plans per tenant.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h3>Compliance Workflow</h3>
                <p>Permit, identity, health, ownership, and CITES-style review flows built into the listing lifecycle.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h3>Mobile-Ready API</h3>
                <p>API-first architecture keeps web, Android, and iOS clients aligned around the same platform rules.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h3>Realtime Auctions</h3>
                <p>Timed bidding, buy-now, sealed-bid, and live updates are planned as reusable auction capabilities.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="home-section home-section--workflow" aria-labelledby="workflow-heading">
    <div class="home-section__inner home-section__inner--split">
        <div>
            <p class="home-kicker home-kicker--dark">Launch workflow</p>
            <h2 id="workflow-heading">The first usable slice is already clear.</h2>
            <p>
                The next build focus is a complete end-to-end path: sellers create compliant listings,
                admins review them, buyers browse approved listings, and auctions can run through the validated deployment pipeline.
            </p>
        </div>

        <ol class="home-roadmap">
            <li>
                <span>01</span>
                <strong>Seller listing creation</strong>
                <p>Animal details, category data, pricing, images, and supporting documents.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span>02</span>
                <strong>Compliance review</strong>
                <p>Platform and tenant administrators approve, reject, or request supporting information.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span>03</span>
                <strong>Buyer marketplace</strong>
                <p>Approved listings become discoverable through search, filters, and listing detail pages.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span>04</span>
                <strong>Auction activity</strong>
                <p>Timed auctions, bidding rules, and buyer notifications turn listings into transactions.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</section>
